text:
Had dinner on a weekday. Food was good, and not overly priced. 2 pax spent $30. Loved their prawn paste chicken as it was well marinated. Claypot noodles were good and not overly cooked. Hotplate tofu was average though as not much ingredients.

Will definitely be back to try more dishes!

The wanton noodle is QQ, char siew are evenly coloured.  The wanton are tasty. The invisible crowd are an expected waiting time of at least 20min.
Closed in afternoon.
Tried the wantan noodle. Always a lot of people que up to buy. Need to wait quite long. Start selling in morning end in afternoon. Don't go too late. Sometimes sold out quite fast.
The economic Bee Hoon & ingredients is 5/10 only. Very oily & chilli is not nice.
New Bee Hoon stall opened in Mar 2020. Previously operating at Bishan Blk 120 with more than 28 years.
